# --- Extra numerical libraries (build-from-source helpers) -----------
 libhdf5-dev,
 libgmp-dev,
 libmpfr-dev,
Description: AIMS OS — Regular track extras (full LaTeX, symbolic, full R)
 The full v2.0 scientific stack carved out of aims-os-math. Installs
 the niche Python extras (mpi4py for HPC, biopython, scikit-image,
 igraph, rpy2, pytables, pygments, reportlab), the symbolic computing
 stack (Maxima + wxMaxima), GNU Octave with the scientific add-on
 modules (symbolic, statistics, optim, control, signal), the full
 R data-science tidyverse (r-recommended, tidyverse, ggplot2, dplyr,
 knitr, rmarkdown), the full multilingual TeX Live (English, other
 languages including African hyphenation, Arabic, publishers, science,
 XeTeX, LuaTeX, bibtex-extra, TeXstudio), GeoGebra for geometry, and
 the extra numerical library headers (HDF5, GMP, MPFR) for compiling
 scientific software from source.
 .
 Install this on top of aims-os-math if you want the v2.0 complete
 baseline. About 1.5 GB on disk.
